title: Do British people respect Mahatma Gandhi? - Quora

response.answer_text: Yes. I don’t know of any British person who thinks that the Empire should still exist. I don’t know of any British person who thinks of Mahatma Gandhi in any way other than “the person who came up with the greatest way to independence for his country.” Even when Gandhi was alive and campaigning for Indian independence, he was very, very well received in the UK. From debating at Oxford, to factory workers in the industrial north of England, he was seen as a fine man with a just cause by many. Now, there are a wide range of opinions about whether the Empire was “all bad” in, say the 19th century.

response.answer_text: Absolutely. Hence why there is a statue of him opposite parliament. He showed that change could occur through peaceful means. He is massively respected.
